article.headline: New Hampshire 64, Quinnipiac 59
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- Blagoj Janev had a game-high 23 points to help the University of New Hampshire men's basketball team win its first game of the season, beating Quinnipiac 64-59 Sunday in a non-conference game. The Wildcats (1-4) took the lead for good early in the second half and fended off several runs by the Bobcats (2-2). Quinnipiac had one last chance to tie it in the final seconds, but Adam Gonzalez missed a 3-point attempt. Mike Christensen added 16 points and eight rebounds for New Hampshire. Gonzalez had a season-high 20 points for Quinnipiac while teammate DeMario Anderson added 12 points and eight rebounds. Chris Wehye, the Bobcats' leading scorer at 17.0 points per game, was held to just 2 points on 1-of-7 shooting.
